#Article about Immutable
https://marcus-biel.com/immutables-in-java/?cn-reloaded=1


Immutable means it doesn't change, period.
You don't update fields in an immutable objects because this capability isn't possible. 
If you create a copy, then each thread will create its own copy, so there is no synchronization issue.